Activity

Up 
get /projects/{projectId}/activities
Monitor project activities (getActivities)
Get a list of real-time activities in the project, such as translation suggestion and translation approval.

Path parameters

projectId (required)
Path Parameter — Project ID default: null format: int64

Query parameters

page (optional)
Query Parameter — default: 1 format: int64
per_page (optional)
Query Parameter — default: 10 format: int64

Return type

ActivityList

Example data

Content-Type: application/json
{
  "activities" : [ {
    "activity_at" : 0,
    "target_text" : "target_text",

    "links" : {
      "comments" : {
        "href" : "href"
      },
      "self" : {
        "href" : "href"
      },

        "href" : "href"
      }
    },
    "id" : 6,
    "type" : "translated"
  }, {
    "activity_at" : 0,
    "target_text" : "target_text",
    "source_text" : "source_text",
    "translator" : 1,
    "links" : {
      "comments" : {
        "href" : "href"
      },
      "self" : {
        "href" : "href"
      },
      "project" : {

Auth

Up 
post /token
Retrieve an access token (getAccessToken)
MotaWord API is using OAuth2 procedures when authenticating or authorizing your API call.

Consumes

This API call consumes the following media types via the Content-Type request header:
  • application/json
  • multipart/form-data

Request body

TokenRequest TokenRequest (optional)
Body Parameter —

Return type

Token

Example data

Content-Type: application/json
{
  "access_token" : "access_token",
  "refresh_token" : "refresh_token",
  "user_id" : 6,
  "scope" : "scope",
  "token_type" : "token_type",
  "expires_in" : 0
}

Example data

Content-Type: application/json
{
  "help" : "help",
  "code" : "code",
  "http_code" : 1,
  "account_status" : "registered",
  "message" : "message"
}

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Authentication response Token

default

Authentication error - for vendor auth, it will also fail if their account is not approved yet. In that case, the error response will include "account_status" key. TokenError

Blog

Up 
get /blogs
Get blog posts - ordered by created desc by default (getBlogPosts)

Query parameters

locale (optional)
Query Parameter — Article language, default en. When no blog article is available and fallback=true is specified, it falls back to en. default: null
fallback (optional)
Query Parameter — When true, and no article is found in the locale, it falls back to locale=en. default: null
page (optional)
Query Parameter — default: 1 format: int64
per_page (optional)
Query Parameter — default: 1 format: int64

Return type

BlogArticleList

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Commissions for client. CommissionList

401

UnauthorizedUser Error
Up 
post /commissions
Returns a commission list of current client. (getCommissionsByFilter)

Consumes

This API call consumes the following media types via the Content-Type request header:
  • application/json

Request body

ReportFilter ReportFilter (optional)
Body Parameter —

Return type

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Newly created project ProjectList

400

FileTooLarge FileTooSmall FileWasAlreadyUploaded Error

405

UnsupportedDocumentFormat UnsupportedStyleGuideFormat UnsupportedGlossaryFormat Error

406

UnsupportedLanguage TooManyGlossaries ProjectAlreadyHasGlossary Error

500

ProjectInsertFailed Error
Up 
post /continuous_projects/{id}/documents/quote
Get quote for documents (getQuoteForDocuments)
Get a new quote for provided documents in continuous project

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — Continuous project ID default: null format: int64

Consumes

This API call consumes the following media types via the Content-Type request header:
  • application/json

Request body

GetQuotesForDocumentsBody GetQuotesForDocumentsBody (optional)
Body Parameter —

Return type

ProjectList

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Newly created project ProjectList

400

FileTooLarge FileTooSmall FileWasAlreadyUploaded Error

405

UnsupportedDocumentFormat UnsupportedStyleGuideFormat UnsupportedGlossaryFormat Error

406

UnsupportedLanguage TooManyGlossaries ProjectAlreadyHasGlossary Error

500

ProjectInsertFailed Error
Up 
post /continuous_projects/{id}/languages/{targetLanguage}/quote
Get quote for language (getQuoteForLanguage)
Get a new quote for provided target language in continuous project

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — Continuous project ID default: null format: int64
targetLanguage (required)
Path Parameter — Target language that you want to complete default: null

Return type

ProjectList

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Newly created project(s) ProjectList

400

FileTooLarge FileTooSmall FileWasAlreadyUploaded Error

405

UnsupportedDocumentFormat UnsupportedStyleGuideFormat UnsupportedGlossaryFormat Error

406

UnsupportedLanguage TooManyGlossaries ProjectAlreadyHasGlossary Error

500

ProjectInsertFailed Error
Up 
post /continuous_projects/{id}/languages/quote
Get quote for languages (getQuoteForLanguages)
Get a new quote for provided target languages in continuous project

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — Continuous project ID default: null format: int64

Consumes

This API call consumes the following media types via the Content-Type request header:
  • application/json

Request body

GetQuotesForLanguagesBody GetQuotesForLanguagesBody (optional)
Body Parameter —

Return type

ProjectList

post /continuous_projects/{id}/translate/{targetLanguage}
Instantly translate your content (translate)
Instantly translate your content with your existing TM and MT resources. This is the primary endpoint to translate your files and content on the fly, especially in CI/CD environments. This is a complex endpoint that is configured in your Active or Continuous Project dashboards. For instance, you can configure whether to use your TM, or translate missing strings via MT and then post-edit those new translations. There are various scenarios you can establish via a set of configurations.

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — Continuous project ID default: null format: int64
targetLanguage (required)
Path Parameter — Target language that you want to instantly translate your file into. default: null

Consumes

This API call consumes the following media types via the Content-Type request header:
  • application/json

Request body

InstantTranslationRequest InstantTranslationRequest (optional)
Body Parameter —

Return type

InstantTranslationResult

Example data

{
  "results" : {
    "key" : "results"
  }
}

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Instant translation result. It may return a list of translated strings, or a list of translated files. InstantTranslationResult

get /documents
View your documents (getDocuments)
View a list of files and documents that you have translations for. This endpoint lets you view your MotaWord account as a multilingual translated file repository, without needing to go through your projects to interact with files in them.

Query parameters

recent (optional)
Query Parameter — When true, this will return the most 4 recent active documents. default: null
search (optional)
Query Parameter — default: null
type_filter (optional)
Query Parameter — default: ALL
language_code (optional)
Query Parameter — searches in source language of documents, in source and target languages of document's quote default: null
page (optional)
Query Parameter — default: 1 format: int64
per_page (optional)
Query Parameter — default: 10 format: int64
order_by (optional)
Query Parameter — default: updated_at
order_type (optional)
Query Parameter — default: null
with[] (optional)
Query Parameter — Attach further information. Possible values 'preview' to fetch temporary preview URLs. This is NOT recommended to be used with list calls. Only use with[]=preview for single document/style guide calls. default: null

Return type

DocumentList

get /documents/{documentId}/similars
Find documents similar to this document. (getSimilarDocuments)
Find documents similar to this document. Optionally, include translation information.

Path parameters

documentId (required)
Path Parameter — Document ID default: null format: int64

Query parameters

per_page (optional)
Query Parameter — Determines the number of similar documents to return. default: 1 format: int64
with[] (optional)
Query Parameter — Attach further information. Possible values 'preview' to fetch temporary preview URLs. This is NOT recommended to be used with list calls. Only use with[]=preview for single document/style guide calls. default: null

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Project model Project

404

ProjectNotFound Error
Up 
get /projects/{projectId}/vendors
Get a list of vendors. (getProjectVendors)
Get a list of vendors.

Path parameters

projectId (required)
Path Parameter — Project ID default: null format: int64

Return type

UserList

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

User list UserList

402

ProjectNotLaunchedYet Error

404

ProjectNotFound Error
Up 
get /projects
View your translation projects (getProjects)
View the translation projects ordered in your account. If you have the related permission (configured by your account administrator), you can view the projects of your colleagues under the same company account.

Query parameters

page (optional)
Query Parameter — default: 1 format: int64
per_page (optional)
Query Parameter — default: 10 format: int64
status[] (optional)
Query Parameter — Filter projects by status. Accepts multiple statuses. Possible values 'pending', 'started', 'completed' default: null
with_pending (optional)
Query Parameter — deprecated. use status[] param. default: true
with_started (optional)
Query Parameter — deprecated. use status[] param. default: true
with_completed (optional)
Query Parameter — deprecated. use status[] param. default: true
order_by (optional)
Query Parameter — default: id
order_type (optional)
Query Parameter — default: null
with[] (optional)
Query Parameter — Include detailed information. Possible values 'client', 'vendor' default: null

Return type

ProjectList

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Project list ProjectList
Up 
get /projects/from-internal-id/{projectId}
Get Quote Id (getQuoteIdFromInternalId)
Get Quote Id

Path parameters

projectId (required)
Path Parameter — Project ID default: null format: int64

Return type

ProjectId

Example data

Content-Type: application/json
{
  "internal-id" : 0,
  "public-id" : 6
}

Example data

Content-Type: application/json
{
  "help" : "help",
  "code" : "code",
  "http_code" : 0,
  "message" : "message"
}

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

QuoteId ProjectId

404

ProjectNotFound Error
Up 
get /projects/vendor
List projects as a vendor (getVendorProjects)
Get a list of projects that are available to you to work on as a vendor. This is not a list of projects that you ordered as a customer.

Query parameters

joined (optional)
Query Parameter — Return only projects that this user has already joined default: null
completed (optional)
Query Parameter — Return only projects that have been completed. When true, this makes joined true as well. default: null
page (optional)
Query Parameter — default: 1 format: int64
per_page (optional)
Query Parameter — default: 10 format: int64

Return type

ProjectList

Example data

Content-Type: application/json

Example data

Content-Type: application/json
{
  "help" : "help",
  "code" : "code",
  "http_code" : 0,
  "message" : "message"
}

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Vendor project list ProjectList

400

VendorNotFound - this is not a vendor user account Error
Up 
get /{userId}/projects/vendor
Get a list of user/vendor projects (getVendorProjectsByUserId)
Get a list of user/vendor projects

Path parameters

userId (required)
Path Parameter — User ID default: null format: int64

Query parameters

joined (optional)
Query Parameter — Return only projects that this user has already joined default: null
completed (optional)
Query Parameter — Return only projects that have been completed. When true, this makes joined true as well. default: null
page (optional)
Query Parameter — default: 1 format: int64
per_page (optional)
Query Parameter — default: 10 format: int64

Return type

ProjectList

post /projects/{id}/package
Package your translated project (package)
Package the translations in your project, prepare translated documents and make it ready to be downloaded. Once packaged, you can download your translated project.

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — Project ID default: null format: int64

Query parameters

async (optional)
Query Parameter — If you want to package and download the translation synchronously, mark this parameter as '0'. It will package the translation and then return the packaged file in the response, identical to /download call after an asynchronous /package call. default: 0 format: int64

Return type

File

post /projects/{id}/package/{language}
Package your translated project language (packageLanguage)
Package the translations in your project for a specific target language, prepare translated documents and make it ready to be downloaded. Once packaged, you can download your translated project in this target language.

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — Project ID default: null format: int64
language (required)
Path Parameter — Language code. You can package the translation of only a specific language. default: null

Query parameters

async (optional)
Query Parameter — If you want to package and download the translation synchronously, mark this parameter as '0'. It will package the translation and then return the packaged file in the response, identical to /download call after an asynchronous /package call. default: 0 format: int64

Package

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Callback result CallbackResult

404

ProjectNotFound Error
Up 
put /projects/{id}
Update project info and settings (updateProject)

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — Project ID default: null format: int64

Consumes

This API call consumes the following media types via the Content-Type request header:
  • application/json
  • multipart/form-data

Request body

ProjectUpdate ProjectUpdate (optional)
Body Parameter —

Return type

Project

Delete project webhooks (deleteProjectWebhook)
Delete project webhooks. Projects currently support registering only 1 webhook. This endpoint deletes the previously registered webhook.

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — Project ID default: null format: int64

Return type

OperationStatus

Example data

Content-Type: application/json
{
  "status" : "success"
}

Example data

Content-Type: application/json
{
  "help" : "help",
  "code" : "code",
  "http_code" : 0,
  "message" : "message"
}

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Project webhook deleted successfully OperationStatus

404

ProjectNotFound Error
Up 
get /projects/{id}/webhooks
View project webhooks (getProjectWebhooks)
This endpoint returns Project entity which contains callback_url field for webhook URL. Currently projects can have only 1 webhook registered.

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — Project ID default: null format: int64

Return type

Project

post /projects/{id}/webhooks
Update project webhook (postProjectWebhook)
Update project webhook URL

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — Project ID default: null format: int64

Consumes

  • application/json

Request body

Body Parameter —

Return type

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Updated project Project

404

ProjectNotFound Error
Up 
put /projects/{id}/webhooks
Update project webhook (updateProjectWebhook)
Update project webhook URL

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — Project ID default: null format: int64

Consumes

This API call consumes the following media types via the Content-Type request header:
  • application/json

Request body

Webhook Webhook (optional)
Body Parameter —

Return type

Project

Up 
get /search
Search everything in your account (searchEverywhere)
Search through everything in your account, from projects to documents, from source strings to translations...

Query parameters

query (required)
Query Parameter — Search query term default: null
include[] (optional)
Query Parameter — Search in these entities. Current oprions are projects, documents, strings. Can be multiple. When not provided, we'll search through all entities. default: null
page (optional)
Query Parameter — default: 1 format: int64
per_page (optional)
Query Parameter — default: 10 format: int64

Return type

SearchEverywhereResult

ActiveWidget - Up

allow_hash_in_url (optional)
Boolean When true, hash params are included in filenames. When false, params are ignored.
allow_query_in_url (optional)
Boolean When true, query params are included in filenames. When false, params are ignored.
auto_detect_source_language (optional)
Boolean When true, we will ignore the source language of your project and try to automatically detect the source language of the given content. This is especially useful in environments with unpredictable source contents, such as a chat environment.
created_at (optional)
Date the date-time notation as defined by RFC 3339, section 5.6, for example, 2017-07-21T17:32:28Z format: date-time
elements (optional)
String Continuous project exclusive elements and rules
follow_user (optional)
Boolean Specify whether we should follow the user around in your website and automatically translate pages.
force_cache_refresh_interval (optional)
Boolean Determines whether to force-refresh local browser cache of your translations in certain period of times, no matter if there is a new activity in the project.
id (optional)
Long format: int64
language_mappings (optional)
String Continuous project language mappings
live (optional)
Boolean Whether ActiveJS should be considered live in an embedded site. Use false if you are still testing Active. Go to your Active dashboard and follow links to your website to actually test Active.
modify_links (optional)
Boolean We can automatically localize the same-domain URLs in your page. The way we localize the URL depends on urlMode configuration. We can either add/update the locale query parameter, or add/update the path of the URL.
name (optional)
String
optimize_per_page (optional)
Boolean When true, Active ecosystem will optimize the script and data flows per page, rather than per project. This decreases the bandwidth usage per script, but makes translation publishing more complex and script serving per-page.
pages (optional)
String Continuous project page rules
path_regex (optional)
String Custom regex for path-type URL mode.
position (optional)
String Options are "bottom-left", "bottom-right", "in-place"
query_name (optional)
String Query parameter name to be used with query-type URL mode. Default is 'locale'.
reboot_on_url_change (optional)
Boolean When true, Active ecosystem reboots itself when url changes.
restricted_domains (optional)
String JSON string for a list of domains that this widget's API interactions are limited to.
sections (optional)
String Continuous project section rules
test_mode (optional)
Boolean Is the Active Widget in test mode? This changes a couple behaviors in the widget to make it easier for you to test and develop your Active integration.
theme (optional)
String "light", "dark" OR custom JSON.
token (optional)
String Token that you should use when you are using this widget on your website.
url_change_mode (optional)
String When a user changes locale (or when we automatically detect and change it for them), we will change the URL of the page they are in. We can do this by actually redirecting the user to the new page, or by simply changing the URL in the address bar via browser's History API. When NULL, we won't apply any URL changes.
url_mode (optional)
String When a user changes locale (or when we automatically detect and change it for them), we will change the URL of the page they are in. We can either change the path of the URL to prefix it with the locale code, or we can add a query parameter to the URL. We also use this mode to detect the locale for the current page when a user directly loads a page. When NULL, locale detection from URL will be disabled (even then, if the user has selected a locale manually, and followUser is enabled, we will still automatically translate the page in user's locale.
use_cache (optional)
Boolean Should we make use of local browser cache for your visitors? We will refresh the cache when Active JS detects new activity in your project.
use_dummy_translations (optional)
Boolean When enabled, we will translate your website with dummy content, rather than actually using MT/TM.
variables (optional)
String Continuous project variable definitions

bin (optional)

String Optional with corporate accounts. Not available for others.

Long Optional. client, app, corporate_card methods require a credit card ID. credit method requires Stripe token and bin. format: int64

String Optional. corporate payment method requires this.s
payment_method (optional)
String Optional. Determines which method to use for payment. client, app, corporate_card methods require a credit card ID. credit method requires Stripe token and bin. corporate method follows corporate account policy automatically, either follows invoicing flow or automatically charges corporate's primary card.
Enum:
corporate
client
app
credit
corporate_card
stripe_token (optional)
String This is required if you are using a one-time credit card. This is the token generted from frontend via Stripe SDK. If you are using a one-time card with stripe_token, you must also provide bin, last 4 digits of the card.
